# 🎫 Ticket Management System

A clean and modern ticket management system built using **React** and **Tailwind CSS**, with a focus on **design**, **drag-and-drop functionality**, and **localStorage-based data persistence**.

This is an interview assignment project showcasing front-end design and interactive UI skills.

---

## 🧾 Objective

Develop a ticket management system using HTML, CSS, and React with strong emphasis on:

- User experience
- UI/UX design
- Responsive layout
- State management using localStorage

---

## 🚀 Features

### ✅ Login Screen

- Simple login form (username & password)
- Stores login status in **localStorage**
- No authentication system (as per requirement)

### 🎫 Ticket Creation

- Create new tickets with:
  - Customer Name
  - Ticket Title
  - Position/Status (`Assigned`, `In Process`, `Resolved`, `Deployed`, `Closed`)
- Tickets appear instantly in the correct section on creation

### 📊 Dashboard & Drag-and-Drop

- Organized ticket sections by status
- **Drag-and-drop** functionality between sections
- **Restriction:** Cannot move ticket to `"Closed"` section manually

### 💾 Data Persistence

- All ticket data is stored and synced in **localStorage**
- Automatically retained on page refresh or tab reopen

### 🎨 Design & UI

- Fully **responsive**
- **Glassmorphism UI** with Tailwind CSS
- Smooth transitions and hover animations
- Clean layout with intuitive interactions

